[
  {
    "id": "JOB.40.1",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 40,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "Moreover the LORD answered Job, and said,",
    "hash": "86763a5555a78d05902a82b7c581e843c02d5950d5258938446fe05a3b344abc"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.40.2",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 40,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "Shall he that contendeth with the Almighty instruct {him}? he that reproveth God, let him answer it.",
    "hash": "7a211d2142a323cd6985133001cd9d5117ac93b0084c69d7855db0a30ead8f06"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.40.3",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 40,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "Then Job answered the LORD, and said,",
    "hash": "742fbd6f157cf6e88b445ea457ec62afeb3d5511b004cf8efdd7e7a63d392310"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.40.4",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 40,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "Behold, I am vile; what shall I answer thee? I will lay mine hand upon my mouth.",
    "hash": "76dbb17903d50c1c27046bb90fbf630abc4cae907f6943cc3aa9dc0bb83c001a"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.40.5",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 40,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "Once have I spoken; but I will not answer: yea, twice; but I will proceed no further.",
    "hash": "de1e37f520a5cfb1974c0e8c0ef286c0c043bd14d721f754464f425ed376a683"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.40.6",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 40,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "Then answered the LORD unto Job out of the whirlwind, and said,",
    "hash": "8be609a094886cd00508c818a56725981c01cf14b4386a7c26c99d5db0ccb8e4"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.40.7",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 40,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "Gird up thy loins now like a man: I will demand of thee, and declare thou unto me.",
    "hash": "81abad39a7c28f1e7117fc6ed4f4da33652a003264d5c80dae9ddd6b8a7b9bda"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.40.8",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 40,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "Wilt thou also disannul my judgment? wilt thou condemn me, that thou mayest be righteous?",
    "hash": "0fad86a83f47612e8e2575ba8616f1b966b1956a380a9e7466cab1cafcde4c29"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.40.9",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 40,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "Hast thou an arm like God? or canst thou thunder with a voice like him?",
    "hash": "3e038aae0424dba6b13df5aa0ac2c3d35f29d4100eac2e48260d7c8eef5bfe3f"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.40.10",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 40,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "Deck thyself now {with} majesty and excellency; and array thyself with glory and beauty.",
    "hash": "ce6eed4d4917f0463107a68a677aadfd8df8e44900fd7d2da7e573ffde6ae412"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.40.11",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 40,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "Cast abroad the rage of thy wrath: and behold every one {that is} proud, and abase him.",
    "hash": "ec0d6d747ef0cdbf0a2aebc4e2b18784f0aebdde373a80c8f0c72a85000ca701"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.40.12",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 40,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "Look on every one {that is} proud, {and} bring him low; and tread down the wicked in their place.",
    "hash": "aa50bac95e33793ca6eff3711ebcaaaeb9fb26c45a45a91b638a4c737b84a026"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.40.13",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 40,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "Hide them in the dust together; {and} bind their faces in secret.",
    "hash": "7272859382906498f11d6a59f304408663ea78c7787f9a638e920d483f8ea025"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.40.14",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 40,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "Then will I also confess unto thee that thine own right hand can save thee.",
    "hash": "7b6123c7133079fa0fe23bce27dd2f35f238a0a7c5c73a7a0255f6a426d5d1cb"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.40.15",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 40,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "Behold now behemoth, which I made with thee; he eateth grass as an ox. {behemoth: probably an extinct animal of some kind}",
    "hash": "6bea3aac914376d3020580785e3cebec407c32cee54eacda3986dc4ceac4723d"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.40.16",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 40,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "Lo now, his strength {is} in his loins, and his force {is} in the navel of his belly.",
    "hash": "4c8e12961dae89597991d6c6e5c20722bc1da0899902440e55c82014f0cc6288"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.40.17",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 40,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "He moveth his tail like a cedar: the sinews of his stones are wrapped together. {He...: or, He setteth up}",
    "hash": "4269e4ab88e0a44196cf0d1d40d3a92468008816a06cf33b52f51b4d9bea0e9d"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.40.18",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 40,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "His bones {are as} strong pieces of brass; his bones {are} like bars of iron.",
    "hash": "3c03be0867771f384d983b4b8f69414356a794170685a3a1b1254a2a8808560a"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.40.19",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 40,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "He {is} the chief of the ways of God: he that made him can make his sword to approach {unto him}.",
    "hash": "4b2d8a2dc72dc9227ed75a60717b18fa50c0622831aadbeb6efce095b6dc2671"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.40.20",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 40,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "Surely the mountains bring him forth food, where all the beasts of the field play.",
    "hash": "5b8e6084c0ae249b84162f713c3da0a37f88dcbfca2ba42f53e8141d7ad74b02"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.40.21",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 40,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "He lieth under the shady trees, in the covert of the reed, and fens.",
    "hash": "ebde175bd18ea46f88089a1a32cbdb073a13b8298808d11dab71692114775ebb"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.40.22",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 40,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "The shady trees cover him {with} their shadow; the willows of the brook compass him about.",
    "hash": "bb392e09b10f6643edf3f564d5b8457588becd6c7f1cae890245217d1dc63d3c"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.40.23",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 40,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "Behold, he drinketh up a river, {and} hasteth not: he trusteth that he can draw up Jordan into his mouth. {he drinketh up: Heb. he oppresseth}",
    "hash": "3b40aeff4383c913a406615308034b4b3306b6050ac878c086214fa852009fd3"
  },
  {
    "id": "JOB.40.24",
    "book": "Job",
    "bookNum": 18,
    "bookAbbrev": "JOB",
    "chapter": 40,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "He taketh it with his eyes: {his} nose pierceth through snares. {He...: or, Will any take him in his sight, or, bore his nose with a gin?}",
    "hash": "be014b016e2dd01fb7c76f98e17b58b769d322896481f54b3536d9d3cd5d1fda"
  }
]